item.title: Donald Trump, Melania's photo with little Tiffany Trump viral. Reason is...
item.description: The Trump campaign shared an old family photo featuring Donald, Melania, and Tiffany Trump to showcase their familial side. Tiffany Trump, daughter from Donald's marriage to Marla Maples, usually stays out of the spotlight but supports her father's campaigns. Donald Trump Jr, Eric Trump, Barron Trump are part of the Trump campaign while Ivanka Trump was his advisor in the previous stint.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Japan: 'Jealous' husband arrested after making over 100 nuisance calls every day for a month
item.description: A Japanese man harassed his wife with 100 silent calls daily for a month due to jealousy. The woman from Hyogo prefecture reported it to the police after suspecting her husband's involvement. Police confirmed he was behind the calls, leading to his arrest. This incident has sparked discussions on relationship communication and controlling behavior.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump megadonor, billionaire says he would pull his money from market if Harris wins
item.description: John Paulson, a major Trump fundraiser and hedge fund billionaire, said he would withdraw his investments if Kamala Harris wins the presidential election. He cites concerns over her proposed economic policies, including higher taxes on corporate profits and unrealized gains. ​“I’d go into cash and I’d go into gold because I think the uncertainty regarding the plans they outlined would create a lot of uncertainty in the markets and likely lower markets," John Paulson said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Gavin Newsom targets AI deepfakes with new law: Why Elon Musk and others think it's a really bad idea
item.description: California Governor Gavin Newsom signed bills banning political deepfakes and misleading AI-generated content. The laws mandate disclosures in political ads, require online platforms to remove deceptive content within 72 hours, and penalize creators of false information about candidates. These measures will help to combat the harmful use of deepfakes in political ads and other content.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Pakistan high court halts verdict in Imran Khan, Bushra Bibi corruption case
item.description: The Islamabad High Court has restrained a trial court from issuing its verdict in the Al-Qadir Trust corruption case involving former Prime Minister Imran Khan and his wife, Bushra Bibi. They petitioned for acquittal, citing recent amendments in anti-corruption laws that they argue invalidate the charges. The trial remains ongoing with notices issued to involved parties.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala Harris-hater Laura Loomer says she's not loyal to Republican Party
item.description: Far-right activist Laura Loomer said she is not loyal to either of the political parties -- the Republican and the Democratic Party. Her loyalty lies only to former president Donald Trump and many Republicans have a problem with that, she said. GOP presidential candidate Donald Trump, VP candidate JD Vance did not endorse Laura Loomer's curry comment but also emphasized that she is not part of Trump campaign.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Train cancelled in Britain after squirrel refuses to disembark
item.description: A British train was cancelled after two squirrels boarded and one refused to disembark. The incident disrupted the 08:54 Reading to Gatwick Airport service, forcing it to terminate early at Redhill. Despite staff efforts, one squirrel remained on board, resulting in the service's premature end.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Vivek Ramaswamy explains who's to blame for 'Haitian immigrants eating cats' row
item.description: Vivek Ramaswamy said neither the residents of Springfield nor the immigrants should be blamed for the situation in Springfield. The community in Springfield was not prepared to handle the pressure of the immigrants who have been allowed to settle there by 'awful federal policies', Vivek said as Ohio's Springfield continues to seethe amid rumors of 'eating cats' and several bomb threats.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 3 grams explosives in 5,000 pagers: How Israel carried out covert strike on Hezbollah
item.description: Explosives embedded in over 5000 pagers by Mossad triggered simultaneous explosions across Lebanon, causing over 11 deaths and injuring more than 3000 people. Hezbollah blamed Israel for the attack and vowed retaliation. Taiwanese company Gold Apollo denied involvement, stating they only authorized the brand and had no part in designing or manufacturing the pagers.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump's town hall event in Michigan: Here are the key takeaways
item.description: Donald Trump held a town hall in Flint, Michigan, days after surviving a second assassination attempt. He praised Joe Biden and Kamala Harris for their supportive calls. Trump criticized electric vehicle policies and warned about job losses in the auto industry. Sarah Huckabee Sanders contrasted her humility with Kamala Harris's perceived lack of it.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Tupperware Brands files for bankruptcy as company seeks 'strategic alternatives'
item.description: Tupperware Brands Inc and its subsidiaries have filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection in the US. The company will seek court approval to continue operations and initiate a sale process during the proceedings. Tupperware has faced declining sales and financial challenges, aiming to transform into a digital-first, technology-led firm.
item.dc:creator: TOI Business Desk

item.title: March for Bolivia's ex-President Morales turns violent, as political crisis escalates
item.description: Thousands of Evo Morales supporters clashed with counterprotesters during a march to La Paz, opposing President Luis Arce's government. The violence erupted when both groups confronted each other on the highway. Morales' followers demand his inclusion in the 2025 presidential election despite a court ruling disqualifying him, deepening political tensions within Bolivia.

item.title: S​​upermoon eclipse captivates skies across multiple continents​​
item.description: A partial lunar eclipse was observed across several continents as the 'harvest moon' entered Earth's shadow for over an hour. This celestial event will be followed by an annular solar eclipse on October 2, visible from places such as Easter Island and Patagonia.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Donald Trump to meet PM Modi amid Quad summit: What's on agenda
item.description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi is scheduled to visit the US from September 21 to 23 for the 4th Quad summit. Although an official meeting with Donald Trump is not listed, PM Modi will engage with key stakeholders in India-US relations. He will address both the Indian community and the United Nations General Assembly during his visit.
item.dc:creator: TOI News Desk

item.title: Who is Sarah Huckabee Sanders? Arkansas governor slammed for 'shaming' Kamala Harris
item.description: Governor Sarah Huckabee Sanders criticized Vice President Kamala Harris during a campaign event for Donald Trump in Michigan. Sanders shared an anecdote about her children keeping her humble, contrasting it with Harris. She also criticized Harris's performance on issues like the southern border and inflation, emphasizing the importance of the next presidential election for America's future.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'He was so nice to me ...': Trump reveals what Biden & Kamala said after 2nd assassination attempt
item.description: Donald Trump disclosed that President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris made supportive calls after a second assassination attempt on him. The gunman was discovered at Trump's golf club in West Palm Beach. Both leaders condemned the violence, but Trump accused them of inciting attacks through their rhetoric, linking it to their political statements.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: North Korea test-fires missiles toward eastern seas amid nuclear expansion plans
item.description: North Korea's latest ballistic missile tests have escalated tensions with the US and neighbouring countries. The missiles were launched from an area north of Pyongyang, travelling approximately 400 kilometres. South Korea and Japan confirmed the launches, condemning them as a threat to regional stability. Kim Jong Un aims to rapidly expand North Korea's nuclear arsenal.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Fake Kamala hit-and-run story work of Russian propaganda group: Microsoft
item.description: Microsoft disclosed that a video falsely alleging Kamala Harris was involved in a hit-and-run is Russian propaganda. The video, shared by a fabricated news channel, seeks to influence US public opinion ahead of the presidential election. This demonstrates continued foreign efforts to manipulate American political views.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
